  "title": "Operations Engineer",
  "description": "<p>1.1 Coordinate efficiently between the asset group, the offshore facility, the engineering support group, vendors and the Client</p>\n<p>1.2 Provide expertise to solve technical &amp; organizational issues</p>\n<p>1.3 Ensure regulatory compliance by following up on Class issues, local regulations and Flag</p>\n<p>1.4 Assume the position of Emergency responder for major incidents</p>\n<p>2.1 Analyze technical and financial data to be able to propose improvements</p>\n<p>2.2 Ensure implementation of optimization initiatives</p>\n<p>2.3 Develop a 90 days annual operations plan and three year Operations Plan</p>\n<p>3.1 Report Weekly to the management team and Monthly to Area Management team.</p>\n<p>3.2 Implement company standards and complete MS verifications off and onshore. Follow-up on the close-out of the suggestions for the Business Process Improvement Request (BPIR) of the unit.</p>\n<p>3.3 Develop and maintain GEMs procedures, processes (be a GEMS champion).</p>\n<p>4.1 Respond adequately to Client queries (with a high quality level)</p>\n<p>4.2 Propose optimizations and brownfield initiatives to the Client</p>\n<p>5.1 Have a global understanding of supporting activities (Health Safety Security and Environment (HSSE), contracts, procurement, logistics, finance, Human Resources (HR)) to be able to bridge gaps whenever</p>",
